>seemed to struggle with lineart
I want to say you did a pretty good job here despite saying you had difficulties, and that it turned out pretty well. When coloring without lineart ("digital painting" if you want to be artsy fartsy about it), it can be a bit of an adjustment as you're pretty much working in the opposite direction than you would be with lineart.
With digital painting, you're working from the inside-out instead of having a defined exterior and working from the outside-in. Best unsolicited art advice I can give is to literally just keep experimenting and practicing with doing that form of rendering until you get a better handle on a workflow that works for you.

Also, I think the trees turned out better than you give yourself credit for, but if you're unhappy with how they look, I would try giving trees a similar approach to how you render hair (large, basic, organic shapes that occasionally overlap). Maybe that would work? Otherwise, keep experimenting with texture and color like have been already, I'm certainly lookin forward to the stuff you'll cook up in 2023.
